description: Cameron Lewellen of Georgia headed into Tuesday's debate one of the small but potentially key slice of voters who are undecided about the presidential election. After, his vote is in sharper focus.
title: An undecided swing state voter watched the debate. It moved the needle

description:
Vice President Kamala Harris was dominant during Tuesday's presidential debate in Philadelphia. Former President Donald Trump struggled to stay on topic and a times sounded incoherent. With the race to the White House neck and neck will this debate make a difference?

For sponsor-free episodes of Consider This, sign up for Consider This+ via Apple Podcasts or at plus.npr.org.

Email us at considerthis@npr.org.
title: During Tuesday's debate, Harris was in command; Trump was incoherent

description: Attorneys representing conservative activist Edward Blum and the Atlanta-based Fearless Fund wrote that both parties “have settled,” asking the court to permanently dismiss the case.
title: A venture capital grant program for Black women officially ends after court ruling

description: It's been two years since the death of a woman in the custody of Iran's morality police led to protests across the country. The brutal government crackdown that followed continues today- with artists, journalists and activists targeted. NPR's Jackie Northam brings us the voices of some of those affected.
title: Twelve Years in an Iranian Prison for a Punctuation Mark

description: After buying Twitter in 2022, Elon Musk instituted sweeping changes — including rebranding the social media platform as "X." Authors Kate Conger and Ryan Mac recount the takeover in Character Limit.
title: What Musk's Twitter takeover could tell us about a possible government appointment

description: Shares in former President Trump’s company plunged the day after his debate with Vice President Harris.
title: Wall Street investors think Trump lost the debate, too

description: Vice President Harris said the economic costs of climate change are already clear, with homeowners facing skyrocketing insurance prices.
title: At the debate, Harris made climate change a pocketbook issue

description: Following the 1989 brutal assault of a New York jogger, the former president took out full-page ads calling for the return of the death penalty. He refuses to apologize to the now Exonerated five.
title: The Central Park 5 are exonerated. Trump doesn't seem to think so

description: Two California artists help grieving communities build floral alters in memory of mass shooting victims. Their latest stop is a high school in Winder, Ga.
title: 2 artists make flower altars for grieving communities after mass shootings

description: Consumer prices in August were up 2.5% from a year ago — the smallest annual increase since February 2021. Falling inflation clears the way for the Federal Reserve to start cutting interest rates next week — likely by a quarter percentage point.
title: Inflation falls to its lowest level in more than 3 years. Here’s what that means

description: Swift wrote on Instagram, "I need to be very transparent about my actual plans for this election as a voter." How much sway do stars really have when it comes to putting the next President in the White House?
title: Taylor Swift has endorsed Kamala Harris for president — will it matter?

description: Blinken and  British Foreign Secretary David Lammy are meeting with Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskyy, who has been pressing the White House to lift its restrictions on long-range missiles.
title: Secretary of State Antony Blinken shows support in Kyiv visit

description: The storm became a hurricane Tuesday night; its maximum sustained winds are now topping 90 mph as it heads toward the Louisiana coast.
title: Hurricane Francine is predicted to make landfall west of New Orleans

description: Nearly half of the water drawn from the Colorado River goes to feed for beef and dairy cows. Researchers say modest changes in American diets could help farmers use less water — and help the climate.
title: Can eating less beef and dairy help save the Colorado River?

description: A flash flood swept away an entire hamlet in northern Vietnam, killing 30 people and leaving dozens missing as deaths from Typhoon Yagi and its aftermath climbed to 155.
title: Flood sweeps away a hamlet in Vietnam as death toll after typhoon rises to 155

description: Nearly half of women over 40 have dense breasts, which raises their risk of breast cancer.  Mammograms should now include an assessment of breast tissue density.
title: Mammograms will better explain what it means to have dense breasts

description: An Israeli court this week rejected a request from Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to block a documentary about his legal troubles from screening at a Canadian film festival.
title: 'The Bibi Files.' Benjamin Netanyahu fails to block documentary from screening

description: From meal kits to grocery service to restaurant delivery, we look at the carbon footprint of convenient food and the choices people can make to try to reduce it. Sometimes there are trade-offs.
title: Is getting food delivered worse for the climate? Sometimes it’s better

description: In Vladimir Putin’s Russia, writing about the war in Ukraine, the church or LGBTQ+ life could land you in jail. A new organization helps authors publish books in Russian they couldn't back home.
title: Russian publishers in exile release books the Kremlin would ban

description: Tuesday’s debate between the current vice president and former president was a clear contrast from the June debate that forced President Biden from the race.
title: The debate between Harris and Trump wasn’t close — and 4 other takeaways

description: Stay on top of your monthly payments and avoid costly fees and interest charges with these smart credit card strategies.
title: 5 good habits to keep you out of credit card debt

description: Vice President Harris will join President Biden on the anniversary of the Sept. 11 with visits to all of the crash sites. Former President Donald Trump will also travel to New York and Pennsylvania.
title: After the debate, Harris, with Biden, and Trump will commemorate 9/11 anniversary

description: Armed officers on campus could speed police response to gun violence. But there is scant research to support this strategy, and studies about racial bias raise other concerns about police in schools.
title: Fearing the worst, schools deploy armed police to thwart gun violence

description: A massive project headed by Elon Musk in Memphis, Tenn., to power AI has moved at breakneck speed. But it's stirring controversy around pollution emissions. The EPA says it’s looking into it.
title: How Memphis became a battleground over Elon Musk’s xAI supercomputer

description: Immigration was always going to be part of Tuesday night’s presidential debate. More surprising was that the conversation veered into bizarre falsehoods about migrants eating pet dogs and cats.
title: The stereotype of immigrants eating dogs and cats is storied — and vitriolic as ever

description: From the economy to immigration and abortion, NPR looks at what the candidates said and adds context.
title: NPR fact checked the Harris-Trump presidential debate. Here's what we found

description: Vice President Harris cited the fact she was a gun owner in Tuesday night's presidential debate, in a move designed to shut down suggestions from former President Donald Trump that she wants to “confiscate your guns.”
title: Kamala Harris is a gun owner — but she's still a proponent of stricter gun laws

description: In a presidential debate, the split screen shot of the candidates — with one candidate speaking and the other reacting non-verbally — can easily become the story of the debate.
title: Facial expressions spoke volumes when mics were muted in the presidential debate

description: In an Instagram post after the presidential debate on Tuesday night, Taylor Swift said she was voting for Kamala Harris.
title: Taylor Swift endorses Kamala Harris in Instagram post after debate

description: Former President Donald Trump cited his close ties to Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán to counter attacks by Vice President Harris in Tuesday night's presidential debate that world leaders are “laughing” at Trump.
title: Trump points to Hungary's Viktor Orbán as example of his support from foreign leaders

description: In Tuesday's presidential debate, former President Donald Trump again falsely claimed that Democrats support abortions "after birth" and "executing" babies.
title: Trump repeats the false claim that Democrats support abortion 'after birth' in debate

description: Vice President Kamala Harris quickly attacked former President Donald Trump on his association with the architects of Project 2025 in the presidential debate on Tuesday night.
title: What to know about Project 2025, as Harris hits Trump over the controversial plan

description: Loomer is known for promoting conspiracy theories as well as anti-immigrant and anti-Muslim views.
title: Who is Laura Loomer, the far-right activist who flew with Trump to the debate?
